10/04/2006
TETOVO, Macedonia -- Lulzim Berisha, wanted under an international arrest warrant for numerous crimes, was arrested in Tetovo, Macedonia, following a joint action of the Macedonian, Albanian and UNMIK police, according to local media reports Friday (7 April). 
Officials say he was carrying a forged Macedonian passport when he was detained. 
Berisha, 38, is charged in Albania with murder, as well as charges related to trafficking and prostitution. 
(A1 TV, Makfax, Focus - 07/04/06)
